1
00:01:43,185 --> 00:01:45,105
ADAPTED FROM THE NOVEL
HIDDEN LOVE BY ZHU YI

2
00:01:52,385 --> 00:01:54,065
I'll go and focus on my great endeavors.

3
00:01:55,425 --> 00:01:56,705
Don't come back too late.

4
00:01:56,785 --> 00:01:57,625
Okay.

5
00:01:58,425 --> 00:01:59,425
Be careful.

6
00:01:59,505 --> 00:02:00,705
-Bye.
-Stay safe.

7
00:02:00,785 --> 00:02:01,625
Bye.

8
00:02:19,385 --> 00:02:20,465
I forgot to tell you.

9
00:02:21,545 --> 00:02:23,305
You should treat Duan Jiaxu to dinner

10
00:02:23,385 --> 00:02:24,625
when you're free.

11
00:02:26,025 --> 00:02:28,185
He's not snitching on you
but concerned about you.

12
00:02:29,465 --> 00:02:30,585
Look.

13
00:02:30,665 --> 00:02:32,705
For the past two years, he kept asking

14
00:02:32,785 --> 00:02:34,345
about your grades and life.

15
00:02:34,425 --> 00:02:35,545
He didn't ask you directly

16
00:02:35,625 --> 00:02:36,825
so you wouldn't feel pressured.

17
00:02:38,345 --> 00:02:39,585
Whenever it was your birthday,

18
00:02:40,305 --> 00:02:41,825
when you got good grades

19
00:02:42,465 --> 00:02:43,825
or during the holidays,

20
00:02:43,905 --> 00:02:45,825
he sent you all kinds of gifts.

21
00:02:46,545 --> 00:02:48,025
He was flat broke himself,

22
00:02:48,105 --> 00:02:49,345
but he still sent you gifts.

23
00:02:50,465 --> 00:02:52,305
Remember, treat him to dinner.

24
00:03:01,545 --> 00:03:05,465
IF YOU'RE EVER OUT SO LATE,
FIND SOMEONE TO ACCOMPANY YOU BACK

25
00:03:16,345 --> 00:03:17,985
I've been ignoring him.

26
00:03:18,905 --> 00:03:20,385
Maybe that wasn't very nice of me.

27
00:03:22,705 --> 00:03:24,505
After all, he hasn't done anything wrong.

28
00:03:25,985 --> 00:03:28,305
From the start, he has been nice to me.

29
00:03:32,465 --> 00:03:34,465
I feel like an ingrate now.

30
00:03:35,505 --> 00:03:36,985
THE DREAM GAMES

31
00:03:37,065 --> 00:03:38,905
Last year, A Dream of Jianghu's expansion,

32
00:03:38,985 --> 00:03:40,905
Fury of Mount Guan hit the market.

33
00:03:40,985 --> 00:03:42,065
The main theme was

34
00:03:42,145 --> 00:03:43,585
an attachment to the homeland

35
00:03:43,665 --> 00:03:44,945
and an underdog hero.

36
00:03:45,025 --> 00:03:45,985
After it went online,

37
00:03:46,065 --> 00:03:47,705
the reception was good.

38
00:03:47,785 --> 00:03:49,625
The players also gave it stellar ratings.

39
00:03:49,705 --> 00:03:51,025
So this year's expansion

40
00:03:51,105 --> 00:03:52,585
is very important to us.

41
00:03:53,065 --> 00:03:54,625
I mentioned this in past meetings.

42
00:03:54,705 --> 00:03:56,905
I hope to see innovation and breakthroughs

43
00:03:56,985 --> 00:03:58,985
in all aspects.

44
00:04:00,185 --> 00:04:02,385
Dawang, how are your preparations?

45
00:04:03,225 --> 00:04:04,385
Everything is set.

46
00:04:04,465 --> 00:04:06,585
Unlike last year's Fury of Mount Guan,

47
00:04:06,665 --> 00:04:08,345
we will be returning to the root

48
00:04:08,425 --> 00:04:10,145
of martial arts fantasy and gameplay.

49
00:04:10,225 --> 00:04:11,625
We will be releasing

50
00:04:11,705 --> 00:04:14,105
unconventional martial arts playstyles.

51
00:04:14,625 --> 00:04:16,465
They will serve as a mechanism

52
00:04:16,545 --> 00:04:18,145
to create more novel stories and content.

53
00:04:18,225 --> 00:04:19,785
I will now show you

54
00:04:19,865 --> 00:04:21,865
the roadmap I came up with.

55
00:04:21,944 --> 00:04:23,265
ROADMAP

56
00:04:23,345 --> 00:04:26,065
I've designed updates to the maps,

57
00:04:26,145 --> 00:04:28,105
characters, instances, and gameplay

58
00:04:28,185 --> 00:04:29,945
around the main quest progression

59
00:04:30,025 --> 00:04:31,825
of the new factions.

60
00:04:31,905 --> 00:04:34,145
I also worked with colleagues
from the Art Department

61
00:04:34,225 --> 00:04:35,545
to come up with a new solution

62
00:04:35,625 --> 00:04:37,105
for the game art style.

63
00:04:37,665 --> 00:04:40,225
I think this theme is pretty good.

64
00:04:40,305 --> 00:04:41,465
It piques my interest.

65
00:04:42,465 --> 00:04:44,265
We should make use of our time

66
00:04:44,345 --> 00:04:45,465
and conduct a player survey.

67
00:04:45,985 --> 00:04:46,985
Now,

68
00:04:47,065 --> 00:04:48,385
it has been over a year

69
00:04:48,465 --> 00:04:51,345
since the last feature technical update.

70
00:04:51,945 --> 00:04:53,385
Does anyone have any new ideas?

71
00:04:56,705 --> 00:04:57,585
Hold on.

72
00:04:59,865 --> 00:05:01,465
I wonder if you still remember

73
00:05:01,545 --> 00:05:04,145
the Celestial Progression System
that I proposed?

74
00:05:06,145 --> 00:05:08,745
It uses an AI algorithm

75
00:05:08,825 --> 00:05:10,345
for self-progression.

76
00:05:10,425 --> 00:05:13,785
It makes the behavioral models
and feedback of our NPCs

77
00:05:13,865 --> 00:05:16,905
a lot more life-like and logical.

78
00:05:16,985 --> 00:05:19,345
It gives players the feeling

79
00:05:19,425 --> 00:05:20,865
that every creation

80
00:05:20,945 --> 00:05:23,145
has its own progression throughout time.

81
00:05:23,225 --> 00:05:25,705
In other words, it recreates

82
00:05:25,785 --> 00:05:27,545
a convincing martial arts world.

83
00:05:28,105 --> 00:05:30,905
But this proposal
had already been rejected.

84
00:05:30,985 --> 00:05:31,945
I don't think

85
00:05:32,025 --> 00:05:33,385
we have the technical prowess

86
00:05:33,465 --> 00:05:34,545
to finish this plan.

87
00:05:34,625 --> 00:05:35,745
That's true.

88
00:05:36,305 --> 00:05:38,625
Therefore, our team came up with a demo

89
00:05:38,705 --> 00:05:39,825
based on pre-research

90
00:05:39,905 --> 00:05:41,265
so we can show you.

91
00:05:44,985 --> 00:05:46,385
You are now looking at the NPC

92
00:05:46,465 --> 00:05:47,825
known as Fang Siming,

93
00:05:47,905 --> 00:05:49,305
whom you're probably familiar with.

94
00:05:49,385 --> 00:05:51,825
It's one of the popular characters
among the players

95
00:05:51,905 --> 00:05:52,905
of A Dream of Jianghu.

96
00:05:52,985 --> 00:05:54,105
I'll now use him

97
00:05:54,185 --> 00:05:55,945
to demonstrate the pre-research effect

98
00:05:56,025 --> 00:05:57,225
of our system.

99
00:05:57,305 --> 00:06:00,465
I will interact with the NPC as a player.

100
00:06:00,545 --> 00:06:03,545
Li Xun, help me with the feedback.

101
00:06:04,905 --> 00:06:06,145
It's starting.

102
00:06:12,665 --> 00:06:15,065
The NPC looks like
he's good at Wuchang chess.

103
00:06:15,145 --> 00:06:16,105
Do you think so?

104
00:06:16,185 --> 00:06:17,465
I bet he's better than Li Xun.

105
00:06:19,305 --> 00:06:21,225
The NPC's reaction was quick.

106
00:06:21,305 --> 00:06:22,145
He's agile.

107
00:06:23,985 --> 00:06:24,905
It seems

108
00:06:24,985 --> 00:06:26,985
that someone has failed to win a drink.

109
00:06:27,065 --> 00:06:28,585
Instead, they owe me a drink.

110
00:06:28,665 --> 00:06:29,905
Li Xun lost!

111
00:06:30,945 --> 00:06:32,185
All right.

112
00:06:32,265 --> 00:06:34,665
I'll pay up next time. Put it on the tab.

113
00:06:34,745 --> 00:06:35,665
Li Xun is backing out.

114
00:06:35,745 --> 00:06:36,625
Fine, I owe you one.

115
00:06:36,705 --> 00:06:39,265
-That's not cool, Li Xun.
-Put it on my tab. I'll pay next time.

116
00:06:39,345 --> 00:06:40,865
A SWORD OF FROST

117
00:06:40,945 --> 00:06:42,305
I'll remember this.

118
00:06:43,425 --> 00:06:46,225
This drink is on me.

119
00:06:47,025 --> 00:06:48,225
Do you care to accept it?

120
00:06:49,585 --> 00:06:51,385
Not bad. He's even flirting with me.

121
00:06:53,425 --> 00:06:55,145
During the design stage,

122
00:06:55,225 --> 00:06:56,705
we set the character's interests

123
00:06:56,785 --> 00:06:57,865
based on the game lore

124
00:06:57,945 --> 00:06:59,385
and the character's back story.

125
00:06:59,465 --> 00:07:01,985
These NPCs are enthused when they interact

126
00:07:02,065 --> 00:07:03,585
with the players.

127
00:07:04,345 --> 00:07:06,105
They can react in a way

128
00:07:06,185 --> 00:07:07,865
that forms a deeper connection

129
00:07:07,945 --> 00:07:09,185
with the players.

130
00:07:10,105 --> 00:07:12,785
But a different player

131
00:07:12,865 --> 00:07:14,905
might not choose to play chess with him.

132
00:07:14,985 --> 00:07:17,025
Is there a way for us to make the NPCs

133
00:07:17,105 --> 00:07:20,065
flexibly handle any situation?

134
00:07:20,825 --> 00:07:22,465
That involves the data

135
00:07:22,545 --> 00:07:24,025
fed to the AI.

136
00:07:24,585 --> 00:07:25,825
Our algorithm

137
00:07:25,905 --> 00:07:28,985
will record every player's
experiences and behaviors

138
00:07:29,065 --> 00:07:30,745
after they log into the game.

139
00:07:30,825 --> 00:07:33,145
So the Celestial Progression System's NPCs

140
00:07:33,225 --> 00:07:36,225
will come up with different reactions
and feedback

141
00:07:36,305 --> 00:07:37,465
to different players.

142
00:07:37,545 --> 00:07:39,385
We could give it a try right now.

143
00:07:39,465 --> 00:07:40,665
We can test it

144
00:07:41,185 --> 00:07:43,585
with a more active account.

145
00:07:47,025 --> 00:07:48,145
Fang Siming.

146
00:07:48,225 --> 00:07:49,265
It has been a while.

147
00:07:49,865 --> 00:07:51,185
Why are you drinking alone?

148
00:07:51,265 --> 00:07:53,145
FOLLOW THE EGRET

149
00:07:53,225 --> 00:07:54,945
I invited the moon to a drink.

150
00:07:55,025 --> 00:07:56,305
My shadow, a second companion.

151
00:07:57,585 --> 00:07:59,705
There's no way
I can't get a drink from him.

152
00:07:59,785 --> 00:08:01,185
Laosan, get it for me.

153
00:08:01,265 --> 00:08:02,145
Okay.

154
00:08:02,785 --> 00:08:04,865
I don't care! I want it!

155
00:08:11,785 --> 00:08:13,145
Bad footwork.

156
00:08:13,225 --> 00:08:15,585
That won't get you a drink, my friend.

157
00:08:17,585 --> 00:08:19,025
Fang Siming is an interesting guy.

158
00:08:21,505 --> 00:08:22,705
Theoretically speaking,

159
00:08:22,785 --> 00:08:25,705
when a large amount of data
is fed to the AI,

160
00:08:25,785 --> 00:08:28,265
it will manifest its own behavior

161
00:08:28,345 --> 00:08:30,625
when the amount of data
reaches a certain level.

162
00:08:30,705 --> 00:08:32,144
This is the part

163
00:08:32,225 --> 00:08:33,945
that AI researchers across the globe

164
00:08:34,024 --> 00:08:35,664
are particularly interested in.

165
00:08:36,225 --> 00:08:38,825
If we can have a technical upgrade

166
00:08:38,904 --> 00:08:40,625
in this regard,

167
00:08:40,705 --> 00:08:42,225
it could be a huge breakthrough

168
00:08:42,305 --> 00:08:43,545
for our game.

169
00:08:44,905 --> 00:08:46,825
But this is just a demo.

170
00:08:46,905 --> 00:08:50,305
If we are to complete
this system successfully,

171
00:08:50,385 --> 00:08:53,465
we need to invest in a lot of NPCs
into the game.

172
00:08:54,265 --> 00:08:57,345
Given our staff
and technical capabilities,

173
00:08:57,425 --> 00:08:59,345
I fear it might not be viable.

174
00:08:59,425 --> 00:09:01,345
If we rush headlong into this,

175
00:09:01,425 --> 00:09:04,345
we might add more risks to the project.

176
00:09:04,425 --> 00:09:06,225
That is a problem.

177
00:09:08,985 --> 00:09:10,425
I need time

178
00:09:10,505 --> 00:09:11,665
to think this over.

179
00:09:12,905 --> 00:09:13,945
Is there anything else

180
00:09:14,025 --> 00:09:15,545
to present in this meeting?

181
00:09:15,625 --> 00:09:16,945
No.

182
00:09:17,025 --> 00:09:18,225
That's all for today.

183
00:09:18,305 --> 00:09:19,145
Okay.

184
00:09:19,225 --> 00:09:20,385
-Okay.
-Okay.

185
00:09:20,465 --> 00:09:21,585
Well done.

186
00:09:22,385 --> 00:09:23,785
You think that will be

187
00:09:23,865 --> 00:09:25,185
a risky move, right?

188
00:09:26,225 --> 00:09:27,785
I think it's a bit risky.

189
00:09:28,705 --> 00:09:29,865
Jiaxu,

190
00:09:29,945 --> 00:09:31,425
there are bound to be problems.

191
00:09:31,985 --> 00:09:33,585
But there will also be solutions.

192
00:09:33,665 --> 00:09:34,905
Solutions outnumber problems.

193
00:09:35,745 --> 00:09:37,265
Yes, Li Xun. Don't worry.

194
00:09:38,265 --> 00:09:39,105
Keep at it.

195
00:09:44,345 --> 00:09:45,625
It's all right.

196
00:09:46,185 --> 00:09:47,105
We've just started.

197
00:09:47,185 --> 00:09:48,145
This is normal.

198
00:09:49,105 --> 00:09:51,265
I'll call for a meeting

199
00:09:51,345 --> 00:09:52,265
with our team.

200
00:09:53,105 --> 00:09:53,985
Sure.

201
00:09:54,705 --> 00:09:55,945
-Keep at it.
-Keep at it.

202
00:09:56,505 --> 00:09:57,345
Your cup.

203
00:10:13,665 --> 00:10:14,985
Jiaxu,

204
00:10:15,625 --> 00:10:17,225
when might you be free?

205
00:10:18,585 --> 00:10:20,145
If it is no trouble,

206
00:10:20,225 --> 00:10:21,745
I would like to treat you to dinner

207
00:10:22,585 --> 00:10:24,185
as a thank you for taking me home.

208
00:10:31,225 --> 00:10:33,025
If you are too busy at the moment,

209
00:10:33,105 --> 00:10:34,025
it is all right.

210
00:10:35,625 --> 00:10:36,985
You can decide the time.

211
00:10:40,465 --> 00:10:42,945
If you are not sure when you are free,

212
00:10:44,425 --> 00:10:46,825
how about next weekend?

213
00:10:47,865 --> 00:10:49,505
I would like to use this chance

214
00:10:49,585 --> 00:10:52,025
to express my gratitude to you.

215
00:11:26,585 --> 00:11:28,385
"When might you be free?

216
00:11:29,425 --> 00:11:30,425
If it is no trouble,

217
00:11:30,505 --> 00:11:32,385
I would like to treat you to dinner

218
00:11:32,465 --> 00:11:34,585
as a thank you for taking me home."

219
00:11:41,625 --> 00:11:42,665
Next weekend?

220
00:12:10,225 --> 00:12:11,105
SANG ZHI

221
00:12:11,185 --> 00:12:12,865
You may decide the time too.

222
00:12:13,425 --> 00:12:14,745
How formal.

223
00:12:20,625 --> 00:12:21,865
VOICE CALL INVITATION FROM JIAXU

224
00:12:23,425 --> 00:12:24,625
JIAXU

225
00:12:34,185 --> 00:12:35,065
Hello, Jiaxu.

226
00:12:35,145 --> 00:12:37,025
I'm free next weekend,

227
00:12:37,105 --> 00:12:39,905
but I'm not sure about the specific time.

228
00:12:41,145 --> 00:12:42,025
It's all right.

229
00:12:42,745 --> 00:12:44,465
We can accommodate your schedule.

230
00:12:46,305 --> 00:12:47,185
Okay.

231
00:12:47,265 --> 00:12:48,185
By the way,

232
00:12:48,265 --> 00:12:50,745
I'll take you
to a phone repair shop as well.

233
00:12:52,105 --> 00:12:53,145
My phone?

234
00:12:53,225 --> 00:12:54,585
Why would I repair it?

235
00:12:55,185 --> 00:12:56,625
Isn't it broken?

236
00:12:56,705 --> 00:12:57,985
It's not.

237
00:13:00,065 --> 00:13:01,745
I thought it must be broken.

238
00:13:01,825 --> 00:13:03,345
Your texts are so formal.

239
00:13:05,945 --> 00:13:07,825
Where did that come from?

240
00:13:08,625 --> 00:13:10,665
You were never so formal with me.

241
00:13:10,745 --> 00:13:12,305
Your words are so polite.

242
00:13:14,585 --> 00:13:15,785
I remember now.

243
00:13:16,705 --> 00:13:18,745
Does this mean

244
00:13:18,825 --> 00:13:21,065
I have a place in your heart?

245
00:13:29,705 --> 00:13:30,545
Jiaxu.

246
00:13:31,465 --> 00:13:32,425
Here's the thing.

247
00:13:33,425 --> 00:13:34,945
My dad told me

248
00:13:35,505 --> 00:13:38,505
to be respectful to anyone older than me

249
00:13:38,585 --> 00:13:39,825
by five years or more.

250
00:13:39,905 --> 00:13:42,105
If I remember correctly,
you're five years older than me.

251
00:13:42,665 --> 00:13:45,705
Your voice sounds young,

252
00:13:45,785 --> 00:13:47,545
but you can't fool anyone.

253
00:13:47,625 --> 00:13:49,505
You're not young anymore.

254
00:13:49,585 --> 00:13:51,265
-So--
-I'm hanging up now. Bye.

255
00:13:52,145 --> 00:13:52,985
Wait.

256
00:13:53,505 --> 00:13:54,385
Hello?

257
00:13:59,905 --> 00:14:02,185
I have something else to tell you.

258
00:14:04,225 --> 00:14:05,065
What is it?

259
00:14:08,265 --> 00:14:09,745
I didn't mean to ignore you

260
00:14:09,825 --> 00:14:12,305
by not replying or calling you back.

261
00:14:12,865 --> 00:14:14,585
I was living on campus.

262
00:14:14,665 --> 00:14:16,305
I didn't have my phone with me.

263
00:14:18,545 --> 00:14:19,385
I know.

264
00:14:20,225 --> 00:14:21,585
Your brother told me that.

265
00:14:21,665 --> 00:14:22,545
You knew?

266
00:14:23,425 --> 00:14:25,185
Then why did you even ask?

267
00:14:27,385 --> 00:14:28,825
Okay, that's it.

268
00:14:28,905 --> 00:14:29,905
That's all for now.

269
00:14:29,985 --> 00:14:30,865
I'm done.

270
00:14:30,945 --> 00:14:32,025
Bye.

271
00:15:24,705 --> 00:15:26,865
CHAPTER NINE, UNDERCURRENT

272
00:15:26,945 --> 00:15:28,785
I CAN'T HELP FALLING IN LOVE

273
00:15:34,465 --> 00:15:35,665
Wait for me!

274
00:15:35,745 --> 00:15:37,265
-Okay.
-Wait for me.

275
00:15:37,945 --> 00:15:38,985
-Hurry up.
-Where is Weiwei?

276
00:15:39,865 --> 00:15:42,585
No idea. She left in a hurry this morning.

277
00:15:42,665 --> 00:15:44,105
Maybe she went to a club meeting.

278
00:15:44,185 --> 00:15:45,065
Who knows?

279
00:15:45,585 --> 00:15:46,505
Sang Zhi.

280
00:15:48,545 --> 00:15:49,585
Jiang Ming.

281
00:15:49,665 --> 00:15:50,665
What are you doing here?

